\subsection{Monodromy group of a Belyi map}
\begin{definition}\label{belyi.group}
\uses{belyi.degree,curve.highergenus.aut.monodromy,gg.conway_name}
The **monodromy group** of a Belyi map $\phi \colon X \to \mathbb{P}^1$ of {{KNOWL('belyi.degree', 'degree')}} $d$ is the {{KNOWL('gg.conway_name', 'transitive subgroup')}} of $S_d$ generated by its associated transitive permutation triple $\sigma$.  This group is the {{KNOWL('curve.highergenus.aut.monodromy', 'geometric monodromy group')}} of the branched cover $\phi$, or equivalently it is the geometric Galois group of the corresponding extension of function fields $K(X) \supseteq K(\phi) \simeq K(\mathbb{P}^1)$.
\end{definition}


